  "texts": [
    "Time evolution of the spin polarization S z c of the conduction electron for different disorder strengths (W/t0 = 0.5, 1.0, 4.0, 10.0) at fixed J/t0 = 0.5.",
    "(a) Behavior for a value of the Kondo-coupling constant J/t0 = 0.5; the dashed line indicates full reversal of the spin orientation to S z c = -0.5.",
    "(b) Results for a larger coupling constant J/t0 = 10.0; the dashed line indicates S z c = -0.25.The spin polarization is scaled by the system size, and time is measured in units of 1/t0.",
    "We use the Krylov method with L = 100, k0 = π/2, and an initial ferromagnetic configuration for the localized electrons.",
    "We use a minimum of 1216 iterations for large J/t0 and a minimum of 2560 iterations for small J/t0."
